Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.60,0:00:07.82,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Under the pretext of an apology for the events on the Bell Tree Express, Sonoko invited us to Izu Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.24,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And for some reason, Tōru Amuro was also there as a special tennis coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.66,0:00:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.08,0:00:23.00,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Through a series of curious events, I ended up resting in the house of a tennis circle,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:27.04,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but when I woke up, an unusual corpse was awaiting me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.51,0:00:34.72,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeking comprehensive answers,\Nhe solves every mystery and code!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.72,0:00:39.10,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Deducing a locked room murder together with Bourbon? Why is he staying near me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.10,0:00:40.52,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.52,0:00:42.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.60,0:00:44.89,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.17,0:02:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I did go to Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.71,0:02:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went there to ask if he really didn't want to eat the {\i1}hiyashi chūka{\i0} noodles I made for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.67,0:02:42.89,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But he said he was fine because he had ice cream cake left from last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.80,0:02:42.89,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kotone Momozono (21)\NUniversity Student
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.89,0:02:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.39,0:02:46.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what did you do after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:51.06,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,After eating lunch with everyone in the kitchen, I had a shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.06,0:02:55.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, didn't my daughter and her friend shower too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.15,0:02:59.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yes. And after that, I was with them
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:03:03.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,until Machi and I went to check on Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.49,0:03:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, when did the spare key for Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room go missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe it was yesterday evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.45,0:03:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd put it in the desk drawer in my room, but it was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.96,0:03:19.97,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I went to check up on Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} with Kotone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.55,0:03:19.97,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Machi Umejima (22)\NUniversity Student
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.01,0:03:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that the only time you went to his room?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also went before I showered to tell him I was about to use the shower, since he'd walked in on me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.77,0:03:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you have your shower after Kotone{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.77,0:03:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.98,0:03:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in his room at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.44,0:03:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any response then either, but he was probably in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.45,0:03:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The AC was on, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.32,0:03:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what were you doing before and after your shower?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.28,0:03:54.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you! I helped prepare lunch, did some maintenance on the girls' rackets...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:57.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, I was never alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.50,0:04:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I went to Ishiguri's room too, to apologize to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.51,0:04:06.51,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Noboru Takanashi (22)\NUniversity Student
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.88,0:04:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to say sorry for the\Nargument we had before lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that before or after Machi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s shower?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.06,0:04:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know when Machi showered, but it was while we cleared up after lunch, before taking out the rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.02,0:04:23.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, that argument was about a member of the circle who'd passed away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.45,0:04:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Last winter, a guy called Uriu died.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.12,0:04:32.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found him buried in the snow behind the lodge we were staying at on a skiing trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was something like two meters of freshly fallen snow there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.75,0:04:44.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishiguri joked that with all the snow, you could survive a jump from the second floor, and he probably took it seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday was Uriu's birthday, so we all got together and celebrated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.68,0:04:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because last year we made his birthday really awful for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.48,0:04:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Made his birthday really awful?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.77,0:05:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around this time last year, we got together at this house and since it was Uriu's birthday, Ishiguri said we should give him a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We crept into Uriu's room from the balcony when Uriu was sleeping, and all let off party poppers next to Uriu's ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.37,0:05:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he got so scared that he burst into tears,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.75,0:05:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and to add insult to injury, Ishiguri recorded a video of him and uploaded it onto the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:24.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.76,0:05:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You three certainly had enough motive to kill Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Motive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only went to Ishiguri's room once, and I was always with you after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.56,0:05:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went along with everything you said, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.82,0:05:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hell, I was the one who told the kid to go lie down in Ishiguri's room since the AC in the living room wasn't working!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.36,0:05:50.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.28,0:05:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in the corridor just after that so I asked him to take me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.79,0:05:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you kill somebody in a room when there's a child in there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.58,0:06:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.59,0:06:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever the trick may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was convinced that the only one who could move Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s heavy body would've been the man, Takanashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.18,0:06:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if all the killer did was sit him up, couldn't a woman do that too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.77,0:06:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they leant his corpse against the door, then let go of the body as they closed the door so he'd collapse...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.65,0:06:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. The rest of the corpse was in just the right place to block the door, so I don't think that's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.32,0:06:36.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't found the spare key to Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.04,0:06:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that key look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:43.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be the same as this key, found in the victim's pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.00,0:06:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It hasn't been reported to be found yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:48.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it got thrown out with the rubbish?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran and I helped take the rubbish out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.34,0:06:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.51,0:06:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though all we did was put it in Takanashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s car boot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.72,0:07:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He asked us to, saying he'd put it out when he got home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.31,0:07:03.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then perhaps the key really is in the rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check it immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.90,0:07:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.73,0:07:10.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did any of the others ask you to do things for them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.82,0:07:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.86,0:07:17.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kotone{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} asked us to put her sports drink back in the freezer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put her sports drink in the freezer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.37,0:07:23.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently she likes to drink them frozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.29,0:07:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, the plastic bottle Kotone{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had when we were all getting worried about Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} not coming down from his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.55,0:07:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was starting to melt, so maybe she wanted to freeze it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.01,0:07:36.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or made it look that way, and the key was inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.56,0:07:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A key wouldn't fit inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.39,0:07:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we came out of the shower, she took it out of the freezer and let me drink some of it, and it was almost completely frozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.82,0:07:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.07,0:07:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who was it that said she'd redo the grip tape on our rackets...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.86,0:07:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We left them with Machi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.57,0:07:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She restrung our rackets too, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.83,0:08:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yokomizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.71,0:08:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't find anything resembling a key in the rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.00,0:08:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.17,0:08:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the sports drink in the freezer was completely frozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.09,0:08:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to imagine a key being inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.72,0:08:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the rackets?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.51,0:08:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked everybody's rackets, but we couldn't find anything like a key anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.18,0:08:29.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of rackets, forensics reported that a number of strings on the racket found under the corpse were twisted out of shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The strings?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.78,0:08:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.78,0:08:40.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the shape of the victim's head injury matches with the bloodstained copper vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.62,0:08:44.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, there was water in the vase for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:45.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Water?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was there water in the murder weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the estimated time of death is about 2 to 3 hours before the body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.67,0:08:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although depending on the temperature of the room at the time, the estimate may be off by up to half an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.80,0:09:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We all ate lunch together about three hours before the body was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so all three of our suspects had the opportunity to carry out the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you sure you didn't see the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were in the room the whole time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was sleeping...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.70,0:09:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you wouldn't remember when Sonoko and I took {\i1}hiyashi chūka{\i0} up to your room, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.08,0:09:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I was probably asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.71,0:09:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said something weird back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.50,0:09:35.55,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He must be sleeping, just let{ that child alone.} him be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.55,0:09:37.88,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's not like he's gonna die from skipping lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.88,0:09:39.01,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:42.85,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The AC's better in this room anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.85,0:09:47.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could you tell from outside the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.10,0:09:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tips of my toes were feeling really cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.81,0:09:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured the cool air was coming through the gap beneath the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.28,0:09:58.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Machi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} said something like that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.36,0:10:00.12,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He was probably in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.12,0:10:02.66,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The AC was on, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:06.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see. That's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.83,0:10:15.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They managed to skillfully create a locked room using a shapeless material!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.62,0:10:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Detective, wasn't this an accident after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishiguri's body was lying on the floor and blocking the door, and he had a tennis racket under his butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.51,0:10:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that mean the vase just fell by chance when he went to pick up his racket?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.85,0:10:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention the room was locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.89,0:10:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you still haven't found the spare key, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.85,0:10:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.27,0:10:50.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're currently searching the vicinity of the house, but nothing so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.02,0:10:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not like it matters, but your handwriting sucks!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.28,0:10:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine as long as I can read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.53,0:10:57.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All right, he's sitting down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.62,0:11:01.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll just tranqulise the old man like I usually do...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.20,0:11:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}? {DENIED}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.71,0:11:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lid on my watch broke...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.75,0:11:15.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Looks like I can't pull a Sleeping Kogoro in front of this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.13,0:11:18.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After all, he's Bourbon, a member of the Black Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.97,0:11:23.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If it came to light that I'm Shin'ichi Kudo, turned into a child by their drug,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.06,0:11:29.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}then even if Vermouth were to keep quiet, they might discover that Haibara became a child too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.15,0:11:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.48,0:11:36.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound we heard couldn't have even been the vase falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.74,0:11:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we heard the noise, the only people in the room were the corpse and the kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.33,0:11:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like the vase would just fall over by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.33,0:11:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So was that noise just the building creaking after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.42,0:11:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did hear some building noises while eating {\i1}hiyashi chūka{\i0}, but they sounded totally different.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.09,0:11:59.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, speaking of {\i1}hiyashi chūka{\i0}, you use ice to make it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.89,0:12:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.22,0:12:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need icy water to cool the boiled noodles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.06,0:12:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, cut the idle chat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.35,0:12:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.19,0:12:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ice melts, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.52,0:12:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it does!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.44,0:12:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if that vase was made of ice, it could've melted and fallen by itself, couldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.87,0:12:24.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You moron. That vase is made of bronze.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.87,0:12:27.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You even touched it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.25,0:12:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.04,0:12:39.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone piled up ice cubes in one side of the vase and carefully balanced it on the edge of the shelf,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.05,0:12:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then once the ice melted, the vase could lose balance and fall by itself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.64,0:12:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if someone was carrying a pile of ice cubes around, wouldn't someone have noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.44,0:12:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.40,0:12:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could even carry them empty-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.57,0:12:59.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While making {\i1}hiyashi chūka{\i0}, all three of them were still in their tennis wear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.36,0:13:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Men's tennis trousers have large pockets so they can carry tennis balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.66,0:13:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as for women's tennis wear, they do sell skirts with ball pockets too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:16.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, even if you managed to make the vase fall,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.92,0:13:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you still couldn't carry the body to the door, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.55,0:13:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There weren't any drag marks on the floor, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.39,0:13:27.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, ice is all slick and slippery, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.77,0:13:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There goes the brat again...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.35,0:13:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.73,0:13:32.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.56,0:13:35.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a racket under the corpse's butt, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.86,0:13:41.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody could've placed ice under the racket and slid the body around!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.11,0:13:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The strings being bent proves it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.20,0:13:45.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.70,0:13:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in that case, there should be water from the melted ice on the floor, like inside the vase,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.29,0:13:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the victim's trousers should have been wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.21,0:13:58.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't find any signs of that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.88,0:14:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.13,0:14:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only there was something like ice that wouldn't leave anything behind when it melted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.55,0:14:10.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, you mean something like dry ice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.31,0:14:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since dry ice is composed of CO2, it'll just disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.11,0:14:20.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, you can't exactly carry dry ice, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.44,0:14:22.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike normal ice, you can't touch it directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.86,0:14:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They had Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} carry it instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.32,0:14:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was probably dry ice in the box of ice cream cake Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said he'd be eating for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.33,0:14:39.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After killing Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with the vase,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.00,0:14:49.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer probably laid a racket with a rope looped through it over some dry ice cubes, and laid the corpse on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.01,0:14:53.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After leaving the room, they pulled the rope to move the corpse to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.02,0:14:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, they left the cord untied for easy retrieval.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.02,0:15:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! That's why I felt a chill on my toes when I went near the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.11,0:15:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dry ice was right behind the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.37,0:15:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, Machi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you said something similar, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.08,0:15:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.29,0:15:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you two {\i1}didn't{\i0} notice a chill?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.87,0:15:16.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.00,0:15:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.54,0:15:23.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that kid might be trying to sleep, so I didn't stay by the door long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.30,0:15:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.26,0:15:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally figured out who the killer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First off, we can exclude Machi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from the suspect list, as her testimony supports our theory that dry ice was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.89,0:15:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same goes for Takanashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who knew the four-eyed brat was sleeping in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.65,0:15:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because who'd be dumb enough to commit murder right next to a sleeping kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.91,0:15:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which leaves the one person who went to Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room earlier than anyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.87,0:15:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,leaving plenty of time to allow the ice and dry ice to melt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.75,0:15:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kotone Momozono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.67,0:16:03.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only one who could be the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.67,0:16:05.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.67,0:16:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.93,0:16:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it okay for you to not do your usual thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.31,0:16:15.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your sleeping pose!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.27,0:16:18.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Rare as it may be, he was just giving a decent deduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.98,0:16:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Kotone{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s crime agenda went like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.44,0:16:29.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, in the middle of making {\i1}hiyashi chūka{\i0}, she hid some ice cubes inside her skirt pockets,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.36,0:16:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,saying something like "I'll go ask Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} if he really doesn't want lunch!" and going to his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.70,0:16:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After clubbing Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to death near the door, she filled the murder weapon with ice, balanced it on the bookcase,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.71,0:16:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,left the room, and used the previously described trick to block the door with Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.76,0:16:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without ever noticing that the four-eyed brat was sleeping in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.22,0:17:01.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she returned to the kitchen, blurting out something like "Oh my, he really doesn't want {\i1}hiyashi chūka{\i0} after all!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.52,0:17:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and having completed the locked room, sat down and ate lunch as if nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.74,0:17:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she wasn't able to fool this great detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.74,0:17:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somehow, he looks phony when he's moving about.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.66,0:17:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.20,0:17:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where's the spare key?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.37,0:17:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key! Ishiguri's room was locked, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.71,0:17:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that, probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.71,0:17:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll turn up eventually... I guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.72,0:17:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, speaking of ice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.55,0:17:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about ice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.01,0:17:38.68,Signs,,0,0,0,,kōri
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.01,0:17:38.68,Signs,,0,0,0,,kōru
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.01,0:17:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do we call it "ice" because it's frozen water?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.27,0:17:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who cares about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.65,0:17:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of frozen water, what about the sports drink Kotone{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.03,0:17:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the key was inside it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.03,0:17:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.28,0:17:58.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I drank some of it myself, but it was all frozen and hardly anything would come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.29,0:18:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then maybe she dropped the key inside before freezing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.54,0:18:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you should be able to see it if you look at the bottom of the plastic bottle, since the key was heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.29,0:18:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what if there's some magic water that'd freeze up the moment she put the key in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.88,0:18:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You moron, things like that only exist in comics.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.72,0:18:19.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.31,0:18:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Super-cooled water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.85,0:18:27.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Water that remains a liquid instead of turning to ice even when below its freezing point of 0°C.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.73,0:18:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's shaken, it quickly begins to freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.57,0:18:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make it, you'd just need to wrap a towel around a plastic bottle so it cools easily,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.12,0:18:41.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and leave it in a freezer at around -5°C for four or five hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.58,0:18:47.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When shaken, it'll begin to crystallize along the sides of the bottle, from the top down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.63,0:18:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kotone{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} likely dropped the key inside the supercooled sports drink, shook it, then once it began freezing, turned it upside-down,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.39,0:19:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,letting the key move to the middle of the bottle before it froze completely, and then gave it to Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.48,0:19:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since sports drinks are slightly colored and freeze to a gel-like state, the key inside would be invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.03,0:19:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then if we melted the sports drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.49,0:19:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The evidence that Kotone{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would come out, I imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.50,0:19:27.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Say something like that {\i1}after{\i0} it comes out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.42,0:19:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If nothing comes out, I'll make sure you—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.34,0:19:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.25,0:19:33.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's going to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.26,0:19:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The spare key with my fingerprints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.01,0:19:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that I dropped the key in Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s blood while panicking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.81,0:19:48.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No way! I took a sip from a drink with something like {\i1}that{\i0} in it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.19,0:19:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did you kill Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.40,0:19:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To avenge Uriu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.28,0:19:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I loved him, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.74,0:20:00.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean that joke of Ishiguri's that Uriu died to try and prove?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.70,0:20:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was dumb of Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} to carelessly suggest that you could survive a jump from the 2nd floor, but that's still no reason to...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.33,0:20:19.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That night, after Uriu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s body was removed, I couldn't sleep, so I went out to the balcony and saw Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, digging through the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.47,0:20:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first, I just thought Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was in denial about Uriu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s death,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.39,0:20:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and was trying to search for Uriu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, who was gone forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.10,0:20:33.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until I saw him pull out the scarf he'd been wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.15,0:20:38.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His smiling face as he retrieved the scarf told me everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.70,0:20:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uriu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} didn't jump into the snow on his own —\hhe was pushed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.58,0:20:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me Ishiguri did that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Uriu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} desperately held on to Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s scarf as he was falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.42,0:21:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He might've planned to go and get him when he was exhausted from struggling in the snow,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.05,0:21:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but two meters of freshly fallen snow would be like like a bottomless swamp, robbing Uriu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} of his strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.18,0:21:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and by the time we found him, it was already...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my plan failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.11,0:21:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make sure Ishiguri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} ate the ice cream cake for lunch,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.40,0:21:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured I'd just fling my racket and injure some random person,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.74,0:21:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I could invite them here and increase the number of people at lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.41,0:21:28.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who'd have thought I'd hit a child's head?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.41,0:21:32.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And who'd have thought he'd be with the great detective Kogoro Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.38,0:21:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps I, too, fell into a bottomless swamp, falling further towards my demise the more I struggled...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.59,0:23:07.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the case was solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.18,0:23:09.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Detective Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.85,0:23:11.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.60,0:23:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how long are you planning to stick with that detective?
